caption: Awesome love this place .  Great from brunch and great for drinks and for cool dinner vibe .Staff is awesome and friendly and the seating inside and design is fire !

Came during lunch time and only had to wait around 15 minutes or so. You get to pick your own seats and your order is brought to you. The ambiance inside is really nice! I ordered the breakfast sandwich. The brioche bun was really tasty.
Meh.  It's an OK after work happy hour see and be seen place, if you're into that.  Pricey.

Had an incredible experience last evening!  Salma was  our server and incredible - attentive, knowledgeable, and made us feel so special with the service and personality.  Food was far beyond expectations, cauliflower rice, salmon, kale salad had beautiful flavors and a generous serving- in fact ..we ordered a 2nd round.  Drinks were well done - started with tequila  happy hour...exceeded expectations on all counts!  Will return very soon!
Excellent meal and service...Saimar excellent server!!!
Virgin hotel is truly the best at surprising their guests with hip food trends. I love coming here for cocktails, brunch, and dinner. A must visit!
Music is fantastic there's always a party here
Not great service, not really sure why but it felt like nobody really knew what they were doing.

It was a very swank restaurant and the food was good but since we went two weeks after their soft opening, service was slow and unorganized. We had to flag down our server a couple times to ask where our drinks were and if we could have the bill.

Dined for lunch there this Wednesday. Between 7 of us we shared 3 lobster rolls, chicken main, calamari, chicken wings, squash soup, several sides of roasties, a kale salad, pear and apple salad and a steak. Almost everything on the menu was lacking salt and was too citrusy. Kale salad had dry apply bits that were to touch to chew. Chicken was too lemony to the point it was not enjoyable. Both salads had too much dressing. The only items that were ok were calamari and lobster roll.
Drinks were great. Didn’t have any food, but the space was clean and well decorated. The servers were courteous and quick. Nice little after-work watering hole.
All 3 entrees were underwhelming.  The service was good, but it hard to make up for the bland food

Don't go here for brunch or lunch, unless you're just getting a simple drink. I love Bloody Marys but the one here was one of the worst I've ever had. Way too salty, no other flavor. Bartender also did not know how to answer some of our questions, nor did he seem to care to find out the answers. The food ordered was not as described. Items were cold, under cooked. Portions were smaller than anticipated. Beautiful space, but just go for a drink or two.
Empty no atmosphere
I liked it. Expensive little salads though.

It was a nice place to eat. Expensive but expected for a hotel restaurant. We were rushed through our meal, table was cleaned off before we got our meal. Food was good not exactly worth the cost but good.
This is a hidden gem on the Northeast corner of the loop.  If you're reading this and thinking of going, just go. Excellent service, food, and drinks.
Great place to start a weekend night out.  Food was excellent and the desserts we have were particularly amazing.  Good happy hour deals, great music and overall vibe.

Tried several cocktails, they were all top notch. They're featuring several  pomegranate juice options for summer including 1 with mezcal and another with vanilla vodka and 5 spice. The fried chicken sandwich was hands down the best I've ever had (I don't like fried chicken and this is what I'll be ordering when I go back - it is perfectly executed). I'd highly recommend the sampler bird cage do you can try several of the kitchen's outstanding creations!
Excellent beer pairing event

(Translated by Google) We had dinner in this restaurant on the first floor of the Virgin Hotel as we stayed there. I start from the negative notes, the restaurant closes at 11pm, and literally chase you away once the time is up. When we sit down, it was late about 21:15, we avevavo put a bit of a hurry warning us that the kitchen was about to close, but not what would happen next. Particular and tasty cocktails. Concentrated culinary offer, but the quality was very good. The sore point is that although the particular environment, very informal, prices are high and the service is not up to what is done to pay. Plates put on the table with two cutlery and a napkin placed inside. (See the photos)  (Original) Abbiamo cenato in questo ristorante posto al primo piano del Virgin Hotel in quanto vi abbiamo soggiornato. Parto dalle note negative, il ristorante chiude alle 23, e letteralmente ti cacciano via una volta scattato l'orario. Al momento di sederci, era tardi circa le 21.15, ci avevavo messo un pò di fretta avvisandoci che la cucina stava per chiudere, ma non quello che sarebbe accaduto poi. Cocktails particolari e gustosi. Offerta culinaria concentrata, ma la qualità era molto buona. La nota dolente è che  pur essendo l'ambiente particolare, molto informale, i prezzi sono elevati ed il servizio non è all'altezza di quanto viene fatto pagare. Piatti messi sul tavolo con due posate ed un tovagliolo messi dentro. (Guardate le foto)
Experience jimi Hendrix for
Amazing drinks
Great service, interesting place.
Great cocktails! Very good food, lovely bar tenders. A bit pricey though.
Excellent service, great atmosphere

Booked a reservation.  The only person that acknowledged me upon arrival after a 15 minute wait was a bus boy who said I could sit anywhere and pointed to a dirty table.  I then had 3 servers pass by me and approach tables near me without so much as a smile.  I was positioned right next to the server station and could tell they were under some stress but I had a reservation and had been there by this time for 20 minutes.  Then the bus boy brought back a water in a disposable cup... at this price point I was hoping for a nice night out not a sloppy bar at 7pm.  I left without dining or so much as a hello from anyone else.

This was a first time going and there was definitely a cute, cozy vibe for a Saturday Late Brunch. Scheduling a reservation however wasn't the best experience for just 2 ppl but thankfully we went late enough and there was some space available. The music a little loud but not to where you can't hear the other person from you. A place to go to start the afternoon party for sure if you're trying to keep things light at the beginning. A little miscommunication amongst staff with regards to food allergies but our server was gracious and apologetic and took the utmost care after that to ensure our safety. The food was delightful with tea time but truth be told, I have an appetite and everything little was not going to cut it. The pastries though were really good, especially the lemon bar. Now the burger was cooked to perfection and my friend loved the aioli. Wish we had gotten the fries.
The staff were excellent hosts
A good casual hangout. Screws younger

Great service. Service was "weirdly great"  almost perfection. Good vibe. Good menu. Appetizer's were great recommend the burrata di puglia and crispy calarmi. Order together located 2nd floor of Virgin Hotel.  Would recommend.
Really good food!
Not quite as good as the first time I went.
Great place for their Upside Down Tea time! Wonderful staff - very friendly and really lovely people
Great environment
Knowledgeable bartenders and staff,  great food.  Doesn't feel like a hotel restaurant.
Great staff and cocktails. Ask for Connor or Nikki!
A bit disappointed with Champagne.
Great place for drinks or to study/ work.  They are open at 7am. Wish they still had the charcuterie board.  That will limit my visits.

Really great cocktail bar in Chicago, a little pricey but the drinks taste amazing. I was honestly a little surprised by how busy it was on a Thursday at 7pm but we managed to get a drink quickly and find a table. The grapefruit mule was delicious and I got some drink with passion fruit and gin, it was sweet and a little tart. I also had a glass of rose which was ok, just get the cocktails ha.
Pricey for the portions.
Great location and good service!
(Translated by Google) Excellent  (Original) Excelente
Lovely hotel restaurant and bar. Great lighting and atmosphere. Professional service. Creative cocktail list.
Beautiful space. Friendly service. Good drinks. A little pricey, but it's in a hotel so not surprising.
Upscale place, upscale prices. Less of books and many are good for a laugh. Will visit again.
Cool decor that really makes you feel at home, bar has mix drink cocktails or alot of different local brews.
Everything about this place is Hip. Loved it. Below is their burrata cheese with housemade strawberry perserves. Wine & liquor list is sick + they have social hour for guests.
They have gotten Gluten free options!!
Beautiful space
Eclectic, fun, bwautiful with great service.
Good.
Excelent place with great view and good bites.

1st time coming into the city and a friend from the Chi recommended it to me. It's a new place and the food I must say is amazing! The shrimp toast was crazy good! It was just a all around good vibe. Good people, food, drinks.. What else do you need?
Such a great place good food, good vibes and such good people working there. Definitely coming back to this place when I visit Chicago again.

Coming from Vegas on a work trip I never expected the amazing service we received from Commons Club. The staff is fantastic, venue is beautiful and the final product would keep me coming back every time I’m in Chicago. I’ll be referring all my customers this way!

I had the opportunity of Visiting the Commons club about a month ago and being out of Vegas I always have a Higher Standard when trying new places. All I can say is, this place is FANTASTIC. The food, the specialty drinks and most of all, the SERVICE all at the top of the charts. I highly recommend you visit this place. You wont be Disappointed.
Great place, awesome decor, and the service was amazing
Octopus was tender and delicious. Drinks were not overly sweet. Nice flavor balance.
nice setup
Terrible service! Even it wasn’t busy! We weren’t welcomed! Servers were super mean!!! 👎🏻👎🏻👎🏻

Very nice setup. The crowd is a bit "uppity" if you will but it is downtown Chicago. Nonetheless, the staff are fairly friendly for the most part. But it seemsbif you're not dressed for the part you don't get much attention. My stay here was completely unplanned so I had nothing but a pair of Jean's and a hoodie. Seemed being dressed like that gets me little to no attention from the bar staff. But still, the other people working were great to deal with. Food was prepped well and tasted great.
Thank you MJ, Yazmin, Luis, and Mackie!!!💖🙂Loving our 1st visit to Chicago🌃service Friendly, Hospital, and professional.
Eclectic and I felt the place like dirty and smelly
The food was incredible. Exec Sous Chef Pha Le is amazing! Great place for drinks and dinner. Try Two Mamas Tambien along with the squash soup.

All I can say is that the Dirty Bombay Sapphire after work hit the spot after a stressful day!!  Enter the main lobby, got up the stairs and then go to the right. The bar is extremely open and the bar tender was attentive. Drinks were strong but balanced. Well done, chaps!

Love love love this place!! Come here every time I'm in Chicago. My waitress, Flavia, was the absolute best. Super knowledgeable about the menu and helpful. The vibe here is really chill and good for that in between casual and dressy atmosphere. The food was awesome, the drinks super tasty, and the people nice. Highly recommend!

This bar is a fantastic place to take clients. The ambiance is sophisticated, while still trendy. They have a wide variety of craft cocktails, while still having the coziness of a neighborhood bar. I highly recommend their charcuterie boards for a large group, as there's enough variety to please everyone. If you're bringing a group of a dozen or more, The Shag Room is a semi-private space for people to hang out as get to know each other (also, the ceiling casually changes colors.) All in all, this is one of my new favorite hotel bars!
Turns out the best meal I had in our three days here was just downstairs in the hotel! Fun, hospitable and the food.....the food.
Drinks are great 🍸🍹
Great place for a quiet drink in the afternoon. Board games are available to play.
Great place, good service and ambiance. Good selection of food and drinks. Plenty of space.
Great place with a nice ambiance! Free drinks for the hotel guests between 7 and 8 pm! Staff is very friendly!
Nice ambiance,  I just have a problem with places that charge  $4 for a diet Coke.
Stopped in The Common Club for lunch and to escape  the St. Patrick's day crowd. I had the green river cocktail  and the corn beef and cabbage sandwhich. Both were  good.
Very pleasant space, do consider hanging out here.
Cozy, unique drinks, great staff and amazing decor. Loved it!
This bar is laid out terribly - if you like to sit at the bar to be seen, go elsewhere. If you can squeeze past it to a booth in the back, they have decent drinks and appetizers.

The bartenders were awesome.  The drinks were well priced.  The atmosphere and decor is really cool.  Definitely a recommended spot for drinks.  Did not try the food but I can only imagine it's really good.
Enjoyed the Commons Club a few times during our stay. Make sure to check out the daily Happy Hour, free drinks for hotel guests from 7-8pm (with few exclusions from bottom to top shelf).
Funky vibe on the second floor of the Virgin Hotel.

Excellent cocktail for me and an effortless, delicious mocktail for my pregnant wife. We didn't have to train the bartender to mix soda and juice like at so many other bars.  Atmosphere is just right for a meeting spot in the Loop: Modern and moderately upscale without much pretense or the overpriced, airplane-quality drinks served in so many other hotel bars.
Modern, yet friendly bar located in the Chicago location of Virgin Hotels. Great bartenders, eclectic bar snacks, and wonderful decor. Go for the comfy couches.
Yummy part 2

Went to the Commons Club on a Saturday night for dessert and drinks after dinner.  The atmosphere was very modern with couches intermingled tables as well as modern lighting.  The dessert was amazing and came quickly to the table. The drinks list was extensive and the pours were generous.  There was also a DJ who kept up a nice parade of well mixed dance tunes that were noticeable but not overpowering.
